.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   How well can a Mage's pet hold and regain agro, pre-50?</span><hr size=1> Hello Magicians and Magician-ettes. <br>
<br>
I asked all of you earlier for some advice on stats and they were all good info. Now I have another question. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I'm planning to start anew on a server with a Shaman, Cleric and Monk/or Shadow Knight. We want to center our healing on one tank (preferably my Pet) so the puller can run off and grab more w/o wasting too much time healing up. I guess my question is, would my Pet (let's say Earth Pet after getting typical tank buffs from Cleric and Shaman and Damage Shield from me) get wasted too quickly? Can a Pet regain agro if the mob turns and goes after one of the Priests, or myself for that matter, heh. <br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=digitalinstrument>DigitalInstrument</A> at: 1/29/03 8:05:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhionsligo>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1283<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 4:42:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How well can a Mage's pet hold and regain agro, pre-50?</span><hr size=1> itll work fine if youre using the earth pet. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
My Character Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=belhaven>Belhaven</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 4:50:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How well can a Mage's pet hold and regain agro, pre-50?</span><hr size=1> If you want to do this, then the Earth pet is really the only sure solution to your problem.  However, if you're using the earth pet, while the other melee (SK or Monk) is in range he WILL have aggro.  If they move out of range, the earth pet (as the only mob in melee range) will take aggro.   <p>Belhaven<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
Priest of Innoruuk on Quellious<br>
<br>
Vermi Pejoratus - Mage on Quellious</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=digitalinstrument>DigitalInstrument</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 4:55:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How well can a Mage's pet hold and regain agro, pre-50?</span><hr size=1> A Pet won't lose aggro immediately if I let the Pet tank and fight for awhile before the Monk/SK joins in? In that case, would a pet capable of doing more than melee (I don't remember if Root is a big taunt) be better? Or this wouldn't matter since pre-50 Mage pets have lower DPS than Monks and SKs?<br>
<br>
When we're fighting outdoors I'll probably create a Water Pet and do Fear tactics with the SK so it won't matter I think, but I'm thinking 85% of the time we'll be indoors and Fear isnot a good idea, heh. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=digitalinstrument>DigitalInstrument</A> at: 1/29/03 4:57:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wrathen@themagicianstower>Wrathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 4:57:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   pet aggro</span><hr size=1> Even if your pet tanks the mob down to before it flees, if the melee person goes in and gets on the mob's hate list, it will be aggro'ed on.<br>
<br>
pets can't be used to MT while someone is in range for the mob to hit if its on their hate list.  Mobs will always go after PCs on the hate list first, then hit the mob if nothing else is in range. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merlota>Merlota</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 5:23:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pet aggro</span><hr size=1> /em glares at the enchanters<br>
<br>
yep, very very rarely will a pet get aggro, and only if there are multiple pets.  havent ever been able to do it reliably and always seems to be with a rogue too.  probably just proper use of evade <p>-- <BR>
[65 Arch Mage] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43048">Merlota</a><BR>
[62 Hierophant] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=152539">Opal</a><BR>
Raid grocer <BR>
food, water, eggs & shards always in stock</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hurk>Hurk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 5:27:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> have the sk tank. they are just as good as warriors, and only lack defensive, which you rarely need outside a raid anyway. you are free then to use more than just hte earth pets to deal more damage anyway.<br>
<br>
I would recommend that after you hit the 20+ range, start investing in a supply of gnoll hide lariats. drop two on a pet to really kick some ass. pets proc often enough that this really helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzabarr@themagicianstower>Azzabarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 5:42:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> If you focus on the puller pulling, and not tanking, things should be fine.  Once a mob shows up, send in pet, and have the puller stand for a sec, not attacking, then have puller run off to get next mob.  The pet will gain agro once the puller leaves.  Clerics gain almost NO aggro from healing pets, so that will not be a big problem.  A cleric can complete heal a pet early in a fight and not get agro, but if the complete heal a PC early on they get beaten up.<br>
<br>
As others have stated, the only reasonable way for a pet to hold agro is if no players are in mellee range of the mob. Most monks and SK's would get bored or frustrated not being able to actually mellee the mobs you fight, however. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzabarr@themagicianstower>Azzabarr</A> at: 1/29/03 5:43:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarlo99>Jarlo99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 5:46:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> I dont think you need to use earth pet for this. All of them hold aggro from caster types pretty easily unless they overburn.<br>
<br>
You can make earth pet hold aggro if you drag the mob RIGHT ON TOP of the pet before it attacks.  When things are rooted they attack the closest thing and ignore the hate list, thus they will thump on the pet-- I havent tested this in a while so may have changed but I know it worked well in the past.  May test it in a few days though.<br>
 <p>Jarly Neverwinter lvl 41 Human Enchantress<br>
<br>
Jarlork Firestorm<br>
Lvl 50 Gnome Mage <br>
-- SoC === FV --<br>
(59 rogue/52 cleric in a past life)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=liesathebard>Liesa the Bard</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/controlcenter/image2/button_help.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 7:31:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> <br>
Soloing - All pets pretty much hold aggro the same, just don't overnuke.<br>
<br>
Group - If any other melee is in range, the MOB will go after them.  Pets really can't hold aggro at all in a group.<br>
<br>
So use your SK, or even Monk for a while to be the MT, then they can try to back away if it gets nasty and let the pet tank. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51722>Muse Liesa Lovely</a><BR>
[65 Maestro] Wood Elf/Mutant Half Elf/Dark Elf/Iksar/Erudite/Warewolf Bard of many songs<BR>
[60 Arch Mage] Retired Evil Pasty Magician of the Super Mod Rod<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aeloryn>Aeloryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 9:35:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> If you have a SK tanking then use any pet *other* than earth. In a group air is the best choice to cut down on healing load with its stuns, water is my 2nd choice for the cold damage proc and fire comes in 3rd due to it's low hp and lack of being hit (but might be good if mobs are cold resistant.) Air and water pets make decent offtanks, and for mobs that arent too tough, fire pets damage shield is pretty incredible (cleric hp buffs would make a big difference too.)<br>
<br>
If you're having problems with the mob aggroing on casters etc. with a SK tanking then it's time to start working on aggro control -- someone's doing something wrong. If you can figure that out pre-50 then you're doing great. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Using an earth pet will increase damage taken by the SK as it will be rooting the mob when it would otherwise be running. In my opinion it's only worth while using earth in a group if there is no one to snare and it's a location where you absolutely do not want mobs to run and you're willing to pay the price for that in extra damage -- i.e. in a cramped dungeon.<br>
<br>
Alyce 62 Mage, Quellious <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322709"><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.shaw.ca/scandrew/cedwhistle.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Helvetica;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>62 Arch Mage, Mistress Alyce (Gnome) <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&lt;GraySoldiers&gt;">&lt;Gray Soldiers&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Dedicated to teaching new pets old tricks.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>60 Phantasmist, Aeloryn Dreamsculptor, (High Elf) Ret.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cydmab>Cydmab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 771<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 9:25:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> You could do this: SK brings in a mob, and SK and pet start fighting it. SK will tank because he's in meele range. When mob is near death (20%? depends on encounter) have the SK disengage and start looking for a new pull. When the SK steps out of meele range, the mob will immediately turn onto the pet. HAve the pet tank while the SK pulls a new mob. Repeat.<br>
<br>
If you accidently get two mobs at once, your pet can solo one while the SK does the other. <p>Master Cydmab Promethean<br>
Arch Convoker of Morell Thule<br>
